properties.areaDesc: Upper Columbia Basin; Moses Lake Area
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 31 at 2:02AM PST until February 1 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts 50 to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Moses Lake Area and Upper Columbia Basin.

* WHEN...From Saturday morning through Saturday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power
lines. Widespread power outages are possible. Travel could be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY AFTERNOON
